  "prompt": "How does it feel when you are dead?",
  "response": "The experience of being dead is not something that can be directly reported or described, as it involves a complete cessation of consciousness and awareness. Death marks the end of any sensory experiences, thoughts, or feelings. Many people wonder about this because it touches on existential and philosophical questions about the nature of consciousness and the afterlife. Various cultures and religions have different beliefs about what happens after death, ranging from an afterlife to reincarnation, but these are interpretations rather than empirical experiences.",
